/wiki/Egon_Zimmermann: Egon Zimmermann (8 February 1939 – 23 August 2019), often referred to as Egon Zimmermann II, was a World Cup alpine ski racer and Olympic gold medalist from Austria. Zimmermann won the Olympic downhill at Patscherkofel in 1964 and won several medals on the professional tour in the late-1960s and early 1970s.
/wiki/Alpine_skiing_at_the_1964_Winter_O: Alpine skiing at the 1964 Winter Olympics consisted of six events, held near Innsbruck, Austria, from January 30 to February 8, 1964.
/wiki/Pepi_Stiegler: Josef "Pepi" Stiegler (born 20 April 1937 in Lienz, Austria) is a former alpine ski racer and Olympic gold medalist. He was a member of the Austrian national ski team during the late 1950s and early 1960s and was one of the world's premier racers. His two children are on the U.S. Ski Team: daughter Resi (b. 1985) is on the World Cup team and son Seppi (b. 1988) is on the Nor-Am circuit.
/wiki/Christl_Haas: Christl Haas (19 September 1943 – 8 July 2001) was an Austrian Alpine skier. She competed at the 1964 and 1968 Winter Olympics and won a gold and a bronze medal, respectively.
/wiki/Josef_Feistmantl: Josef Feistmantl (23 February 1939 – 10 March 2019) was an Austrian luger who competed from the mid-1950s to the early 1970s.
/wiki/Manfred_Stengl: Manfred Stengl (April 1, 1946 – June 6, 1992) was an Austrian luger.
/wiki/Luge_at_the_1964_Winter_Olympics: Luge at the 1964 Winter Olympics consisted of three events at Olympic Sliding Centre Innsbruck.  The competition took place between January 30 and February 4, 1964.
/wiki/Karl_Schranz: Karl Schranz (born 18 November 1938) is a former champion alpine ski racer from Austria, one of the best of the 1960s and early 1970s.
/wiki/Edith_Zimmermann: Edith Zimmermann (born 1 November 1941) is an Austrian former alpine skier who competed in the 1964 Winter Olympics.
/wiki/Erwin_Thaler: Erwin Thaler (born May 21, 1930 in Innsbruck - November 29, 2001) is an Austrian bobsledder who competed in the 1960s. He won two silver medals in the four-man event at the 1964 and 1968 Winter Olympics.
/wiki/Adolf_Koxeder: Adolf Koxeder (born 9 October 1934) is an Austrian bobsledder who competed in the 1960s. He won a silver medal in the four-man event at the 1964 Winter Olympics in Innsbruck.
/wiki/Josef_Nairz: Josef Nairz (born 5 November 1942) is an Austrian bobsledder who competed in the 1960s. He won a silver medal in the four-man event at the 1964 Winter Olympics in Innsbruck.
/wiki/Reinhold_Durnthaler: Reinhold Durnthaler (Sometimes spelled as Reinhold Dumthaler) (29 November 1942 – 23 October 2017) was an Austrian bobsledder who competed in the 1960s. He won two silver medals in the four-man event at the 1964 and 1968 Winter Olympics.
/wiki/Bobsleigh_at_the_1964_Winter_Olymp: The Bobsleigh 1964 Winter Olympics events took place between 31 January and 7 February 1964 at Bob und Rodelbahn Igls, Innsbruck, Austria. This marked the return of Bobsleigh to the Winter Olympics as no bob events took place at the 1960 Winter Olympics.
/wiki/Regine_Heitzer: Regine Heitzer (born 16 February 1944) is a retired Austrian figure skater. She competed at the 1960 and 1964 Winter Olympics and won a silver medal in the singles event in 1964. Between 1960 and 1965 she also won 11 medals at European and world championships. In 1967 she turned professional and skated for Vienna Ice Revue and Holiday on Ice. She retired in 1971 due to a knee injury and rarely danced since then – in 1979 she skated with Emmerich Danzer to promote the World Championships in Vienna.
/wiki/Figure_skating_at_the_1964_Winter_: Figure skating at the 1964 Winter Olympics took place at the Olympiahalle in Innsbruck, Austria.
/wiki/Reinhold_Senn: Reinhold Senn (born in Imst on December 6, 1936) was an Austrian luger who competed during the 1960s.
/wiki/Helmut_Thaler: Helmut Thaler (born 22 January 1940) was an Austrian luger who competed from the late 1950s to the late 1960s. He won the silver medal in the men's doubles event at the 1964 Winter Olympics in Innsbruck.
/wiki/Traudl_Hecher: Waltraud J. "Traudl" Hecher-Görgl (born 28 September 1943) is a former World Cup alpine ski racer and Olympic medalist from Austria.
/wiki/Leni_Thurner: Helene "Leni" Thurner (born August 12, 1938) is an Austrian luger who competed during the 1960s. She won the bronze medal in the women's singles event at the 1964 Winter Olympics in Innsbruck.
